1.title: Getting Warped Up
1.plot: New roadies, new relationships and over a hundred bands, including Reel Big Fish, Echosmith and New Years Day.

2.title: Terry Is an Idiot
2.plot: The Aquabats overstay their welcome on Kenny's stage, while Lindsay receives some unwelcome news from Terry.

3.title: Young and the Wrestless
3.plot: While archrivals Anto (The Swellers) and J.J.R. (The Wonder Years) wrestle each other, Mike, Lindsay and Danny wrestle with their relationships.

4.title: Oh. Canada.
4.plot: Beebs fulfills a longtime dream by singing with her favorite band, while a trip across the border turns into a nightmare for Danny.

5.title: Save the Kings!
5.plot: Danny comes to the rescue for UK band Alvarez Kings when their singer gets stuck in Canada.

6.title: The Oprah Episode
6.plot: The Summer Set help Kacie deliver a "Dream Day," while Beebs meets her biological brother for the first time.

7.title: Return of the King
7.plot: The Alvarez Kings reunite with their singer, and the catering band gets a chance to step out of the kitchen and onto the stage.

8.title: Loser Leaves Warped Tour
8.plot: Danny recruits The Used for Sierra's birthday surprise, while wrestling rivals JJR (The Wonder Years) and Anto (The Swellers) engage in their final bout of the summer.

9.title: The Perfect Storm
9.plot: Hard-partying band Crossfaith test Kevin's limits, and a thunderstorm sends a jolt of electricity into the Acoustic Basement.

10.title: Sweaty Hugs
10.plot: Kenny tries to tame the band letlive.'s unpredictable frontman, while Beebs tries to tame a badly timed sickness.

11.title: Race for the Crown
11.plot: It's Prom! The biggest event at Warped Tour and things get awkward as people scramble to find dates and the competition for Prom Queen gets fierce.

12.title: All Warped Up Inside
12.plot: It's an emotional last day of Warped Tour as people say goodbye and look back at their fondest memories.

1.title: Let's Get Warped
1.plot: In episode 1 we converge upon Salt Lake City, Utah where the massive music festival, the Vans Warped Tour is about to kick off it's first show of the summer. They are expecting nearly fifteen thousand fans at the first show, so the roadies must shake off the dust and get into work-mode fast. The day starts off well but in true Warped Tour fashion there are always roadblocks that we must overcome daily. Danny, the Setup Crew Chief squares off with an uncooperative sponsor vehicle and the pneumatic lift meant to display it. Later, first time Main Stage Manager, Kenny ...

2.title: San Francisco
2.plot: The roadies set their sights on San Francisco, and today is a special one because if the roadies can make it through the day they know that the 2012 Warped Prom awaits them.

3.title: Phoenix
3.plot: When you wake up in Phoenix, AZ and the morning temperature is already in triple digits you know that it's not going to be an easy day. Mix with that massive delays in the morning set up and you have one of the toughest days these roadies will see all summer. Tempers begin to flare and Tour Producer and Founder sees that he needs to step in and take charge before the fans get restless, let's hope that it's not too little too late.

4.title: Montreal
4.plot: We are gearing up for the Canadian leg of the tour, and getting 1000+ bands and crew to cross the border is no easy task. Key members of the Set Up Crew find out that they can't go to Canada, thus leaving their team to trudge on without them.

5.title: Toronto
5.plot: With one Canada show down and one more to go, the crew rolls on to Toronto. The day starts like any other; well, actually unlike any other if you consider how smooth set up went. But the easy going day quickly comes to a halt when a major storm sweeps into Montreal and an emergency scenario starts to unfold quickly.

6.title: Buffalo
6.plot: Reunited and it feels so good...or does it? After Danny and the boys return to the tour after being away from the rest of the crew, the happy reunion turns sour as he finds out there was some trash-talking while he was galavanting in New York City. Meanwhile, Kenny is having a difficult day as well, the pressure is on for him to prove himself worthy of the main stage manager title and today is proving to be quite difficult. The boys are being tested today for sure the question is how will they handle the pressure.

7.title: Las Vegas
7.plot: An after show party in Colorado goes late into the night, perhaps not the best move when working in the sun for 12 hours the following day. These road warriors work hard together and they play hard together.

8.title: St. Petersburg
8.plot: We're in Florida and have rounded the corner nearing the final weeks of this crazy adventure. What should be a joyous time is now tainted as a member of the Set Up Crew has missed load in for the day, causing Danny to have to choose between being a friend, and being a boss. Later, the boys must say goodbye to a key member of the crew as he is leaving the tour early.

9.title: From Milwaukee to Seattle
9.plot: The tour is coming to an end and the wear and tear of the road is setting in. Being on tour for two months takes a physical and emotional toll on your mind and body. Mistakes start happening within the road weary crew and while driving to our next stop there is an accident forcing one of the drivers to unfortunately head home early. From exhaustion to injuries - everyone is drained and it's a giant roller coaster of emotions that the whole crew is ready to get off of.

10.title: Portland
10.plot: It's the last day of punk rock summer camp, and sadly it's time to put a wrap on Warped Tour 2012. Unfortunately for the Warped roadies, the last day is turning out to be the worst and hardest day they will have all summer. We're in Portland, OR and we are in hell. Everything and anything that could go wrong - does. While the crew deals with all of the obstacles of making this last show actually go on, they are also dealing with the bittersweet feelings about tour ending and having to say their goodbyes. It's a time to reflect on this past summer - the ups, the downs,...

imdb.plot outline: A behind-the-scenes look at the inner workings of the Vans Warped Tour as it travels across the country with more than 60 bands. With the rollout of ten episodes this fall, viewers will get to experience firsthand what it's like for the young crew that keeps the tour rolling from city to city, while trying to enjoy the greatest, and yet most challenging, summer of their lives.
